
msgid "Tarantool 2.10.7"
msgstr ""

msgid "Released on 2023-05-24."
msgstr ""

msgid "Release: :tarantool-release:`2.10.7`."
msgstr ""

msgid "Tag: ``2.10.7``."
msgstr ""

msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"2.10.7 is the 8th :doc:`stable </release/policy/>` version of the 2.10 "
"release series. It resolves 17 bugs since 2.10.6."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"The “stable” label means that we have all planned features implemented and "
"we see no high-impact issues. However, if you encounter an issue, feel free "
"to `report it <https://github.com/tarantool/tarantool/issues>`__ on GitHub."
msgstr ""

msgid "Compatibility"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Tarantool 2.x is backward compatible with Tarantool 1.10.x in the binary "
"data layout, client-server protocol, and replication protocol."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Please :doc:`upgrade </book/admin/upgrades>` using the "
"``box.schema.upgrade()`` procedure to unlock all the new features of the 2.x"
" series."
msgstr ""

msgid "Bugs fixed"
msgstr ""

msgid "Core"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a crash that could happen when preparing a crash report on macOS "
"(:tarantool-issue:`8445`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed an integer overflow issue in ``net.box`` (:tarantool-sec-issue:`121`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"An ``IPROTO_EVENT`` packet now has the same sync number as the last "
"corresponding ``IPROTO_WATCH`` request (:tarantool-issue:`8393`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug because of which a dirty (not committed to WAL) DDL record could"
" be written to a snapshot and cause a recovery failure (:tarantool-"
"issue:`8530`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Replication"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug that occurred on applier failure: a node could start an election"
" without having a quorum to do this (:tarantool-issue:`8433`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Now if a join fails with some non-critical error, such as ``ER_READONLY``, "
"``ER_ACCESS_DENIED``, or something network-related, the instance tries to "
"find a new master to join off and tries again (:tarantool-issue:`6126`, "
":tarantool-issue:`8681`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"States when joining a replica are renamed. Now the value of "
"``box.info.replication[id].upstream.status`` during join can be either "
"``wait_snapshot`` or ``fetch_snapshot`` instead of ``initial_join`` "
"(:tarantool-issue:`6126`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed replicaset bootstrap getting stuck on some nodes with ``ER_READONLY`` "
"when there are connectivity problems (:tarantool-issue:`7737`, :tarantool-"
"issue:`8681`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a bug when a replicaset state machine that is tracking the number of "
"appliers according to their states could become inconsistent during "
"reconfiguration (:tarantool-issue:`7590`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "LuaJIT"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Backported patches from the vanilla LuaJIT trunk (:tarantool-issue:`8069`, "
":tarantool-issue:`8516`). The following issues were fixed as part of this "
"activity:"
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed ``emit_rma()`` for x64/GC64 mode for non-``mov`` instructions."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Limited Lua C library path with the default ``PATH_MAX`` value of 4096 "
"bytes."
msgstr ""

msgid "Fixed assembling of ``IR_LREF`` assembling for GC64 mode on x86_64."
msgstr ""

msgid "SQL"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed an assertion when selecting tuples with incomplete internal format "
"(:tarantool-issue:`8418`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed integer overflow issues in built-in functions (:tarantool-sec-"
"issue:`119`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed a possible assertion or segmentation fault when optimizing ``INSERT "
"INTO ... SELECT FROM`` (:tarantool-issue:`8661`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed an integer overflow issue and added check for the ``printf()`` failure"
" due to too large size (:tarantool-sec-issue:`122`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Datetime"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed an error in ``datetime.set`` when ``timestamp`` is passed along with "
"``nsec``, ``usec``, or ``msec`` (:tarantool-issue:`8583`)."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Fixed errors when the string representation of a datetime object had a "
"negative nanosecond part (:tarantool-issue:`8570`)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Build"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Enabled compiler optimizations for static build dependencies, which were "
"erroneously disabled in version 2.10.3 (:tarantool-issue:`8606`)."
msgstr ""
